The default behavior in `shiny::actionButton()` is to open a web link in the *current* window. This approach has two potential implications for user-experience:

1.  The current progress within the shiny app will be lost; clicking üîô on your browser will reload the app üò≠
2.  This can (independent of #1) inadvertently divert users away from your app üèÉÔ∏èüí®

