So what can we do?

‚úñÔ∏è Do nothing. Leave it as is and let all the hard work you put into the app be overshadowed by the site your are linking to.

‚úîÔ∏è Make the link open in a new tab or window.

‚úîÔ∏è Force the link to open in a new window.

The distinction between the two latter choices boils down to a users default browser settings. If you use Chrome like me, opening a link (designed to open in a tab or new window) defaults to opening it in a new tab. For you, it *might* open in a new window. Who knows? üé±

If you really need the link to open in a separate window, luckily with a little elbow grease we can make that a sure thing.üéØ We just need to explicitly specify the window `height` and `width`. You can also pass `fullscreen=1` to make the new window, well, full screen. See the code snippet below.

> ‚ö†Ô∏èOpening links in a new window may result in getting dinged by an ad-blocker. This is because the so-called new window is more of a pop-up rather than it being a truly new window (i.e. `CTRL + N`).

Thank you [iqis](https://github.com/iqis) for pointing out that! üëΩÔ∏è

Below, I have three buttons and their corresponding code you might use in a shiny app. It's pretty straight forward so I'll end with saying keep user-experience front and center in your design! ‚úåüçª

```{r, echo = T, eval = F}
# Default - current
shiny::actionButton('btn1',
                    'Current Window',
                    onclick ="location.href='http://google.com';")

# New tab or window  
shiny::actionButton('btn2',
                    'New Window or Tab', 
                    onclick ="window.open('http://google.com', '_blank')")

# New window
shiny::actionButton('btn3',
                    'New Window', 
                    onclick ="window.open('http://google.com', '_blank','width=800,height=800')")
```

```{r, echo = F, eval = T}
shiny::actionButton('btn1',
                    'Current Window',
                    class = "btn btn-danger btn-lg  btn-huge",
                    onclick ="location.href='http://google.com';")
shiny::HTML('&nbsp;')
shiny::actionButton('btn2',
                    'New Window or Tab', 
                    class = "btn btn-warning btn-lg  btn-huge",
                    onclick ="window.open('http://google.com', '_blank')")
shiny::HTML('&nbsp;')
shiny::actionButton('btn3',
                    'New Window', 
                    class = "btn btn-success btn-lg  btn-huge",
                    onclick ="window.open('http://google.com', '_blank','width=800,height=800')")
```
